{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":291845,"duration_api_ms":277642,"num_turns":25,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"a3a1bf28-f020-4c34-b1f8-6aaeff5f9925","total_cost_usd":1.0999202499999998,"usage":{"input_tokens":18,"cache_creation_input_tokens":55723,"cache_read_input_tokens":821423,"output_tokens":13634,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":55723,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":18,"outputTokens":13634,"cacheReadInputTokens":821423,"cacheCreationInputTokens":55723,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.0999202499999998,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"amendments":[{"body":"Auto-populated plan_hash from snapshot can cause false-positive rejection on terminal replay after plan evolution. Scenario: (1) bead completed with plan_hash=None, auto-populated to snapshot's hash_v1; (2) new plan persisted, snapshot.plan_hash becomes hash_v2; (3) terminal replay of same completion with plan_hash=None auto-populates to hash_v2; (4) `option_conflicts(Some(hash_v1), Some(hash_v2))` at fs.rs:3161 triggers an `incompatible_terminal_update` error, breaking idempotent replay. Pre-change, the replay would pass None through to the adapter where `option_conflicts(Some(x), None)` is always false. Fix: either skip auto-population in `update_task_run` when the entry is already terminal (requires a two-phase check or passing the original caller value alongside the effective value), or weaken the terminal replay conflict check to treat plan_hash mismatch as non-fatal when the stored entry already has a plan_hash (backfill-only semantics, matching run_id behavior).","rationale":"Terminal replay idempotency is a core safety property — the existing code comments and tests explicitly document that replaying a completed entry with compatible values must succeed. The auto-population change breaks this contract in a narrow but real window (plan update between original completion and replay after crash recovery). The error is not silent — it produces a CorruptRecord error — but it prevents crash-recovery replay from succeeding, which could leave snapshot/journal state permanently inconsistent."}],"summary":"Reviewed all three fixes (journal struct drift detection, runless-to-named completion, plan_hash auto-population). All 683 tests pass. Issues 1 and 2 are correctly implemented: the round-trip tests catch struct drift in either direction (compile-time for signature changes, runtime for field-set divergence via render equality check), and the runless backfill correctly uses `get_or_insert_with` with plan_hash conflict protection. Issue 3's auto-population logic is correct for first-write paths (caller-provided takes precedence via `.map().or_else()`), but introduces a regression in terminal replay idempotency: when a plan is updated after a bead's original completion, a crash-recovery replay that omits plan_hash will auto-populate the new plan's hash, which conflicts with the stored hash and fails the `incompatible_terminal_update` check."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"f7ef4824-2c47-4c11-84dd-cd913e04ee23"}
